[SN]TITLE[SN]
People advised to avoid River Ystwyth due to fallen metal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
People are being advised to avoid a stretch of a Ceredigion river due to fallen sharp metal sheets.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Natural Resources Wales (NRW) tweeted the warning advising kayakers to stay away from the River Ystwyth near Riverside Sawmill in Llanafan.
NRW said it is investigating where the sheets came from.
Warning signs have been put up and officers will assess next week whether the metal can be retrieved.
